data.title: Rock On The Net: Timbaland Info Page
data.text:
Timbaland & Magoo: Welcome To Our WorldReleased: October 28, 1997

US: Platinum

Billboard Top 200 LPs peak: # 33

Tracks: "Beep Beep" - "Feel It" - "Up Jumps Da' Boogie" - "Clock Strikes" - "15 After Da' Hour" - "Ms. Parker" (with Luve Jon) - "Luv 2 Luv U" (Remix) (with Shaunta Montgomery & Playa) - "Luv 2 Luv U" (with St. Nick & Playa) - "Smoke In Da' Air" (with Playa) - "Intro Buddha" (with Buddha Brother, Big B & DJ Law) - "Peepin' My Style" - "Writtin' Rhymes" - "Deep In Your Memory" - "Clock Strikes" (Remix) - "Sex Beat" (Interlude) - "Man Undercover" (with Aaliyah & Missy Elliott) - "Joy" (with Ginuwine & Playa) - "Up Jumps Da' Boogie" (Remix) (with Missy Elliott)

Kirkland) - "Get It On" (with Bassey) - "To My" (with Nas & Mad Skillz) - "Here We Come" (with Magoo & Missy Elliott) - "Wit' Yo' Bad Self" (with Mad Skillz) - "Lobster & Scrimp" (with Jay-Z) - "What Cha Know About This" (with Moca & Baby Blue) - "Can't Nobody" (with 1 Life 2 Live) - "What Cha Talkin' Bout" (with Lil' Man, Static & Magoo) - "Put 'Em On" (with Static & Yaushameen Michael) - "Fat Rabbit" (with Ludacris) - "Who Am I" (with Twista) - "Talking On The Phone" (with Kelly Price, Missy Elliott & Lil' Man) - "Keep It Real" (with Ginuwine) - "John Blaze" (with Aaliyah & Missy Elliott) - "Birthday" (with Playa) - "3:30 In The Morning" (with Virginia Williams) - "Outro" - "Bringin' It" (with Troy Mitchell)
